<subSubSection id="AEDFC70E7994E7C7E845DDD497475EF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D260F88B9C189BFAA3A79FA3662099FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A96CE101A6C817448B18474641AB4FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="C977D10120DF52609F521FC1A5BEF5CE" baseAuthorityName="Mao" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster arugosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arugosus">
<emphasis id="9A335E4E6EA323C96ECA160B90B46DD3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster arugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly identical to 
<taxonomicName id="9FBEC9CD34AAAC12F8CB65C8F8C5753F" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. pullus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullus">
<emphasis id="58AC675153C7A47F29A6DD30417ADD5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. pullus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The members of both species possess dark head and metasoma with pale metasoma. As 
<bibRefCitation id="BBC8172CDFED2B08C35AC441441DC7E1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.99-3237.229" author="Mao, YT" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="229 - 266" refId="B8" refString="Mao, YT, 1949. The species of ichneumon-flies of the genus Cardiochiles occurring in America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 99 (3237): 229 - 266, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.99-3237.229" title="The species of ichneumon-flies of the genus Cardiochiles occurring in America north of Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.99-3237.229" volume="99" year="1949">Mao (1949)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned, 
<taxonomicName id="C4F5785216B552C50FD8B7DBCF0F3CE2" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. arugosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arugosus">
<emphasis id="E8F7C20E56D6A2EDBF0257BF08059835" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. arugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D0BFA3B5ED908821C1F17AF5F4150846" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. pullus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullus">
<emphasis id="426A40D8178094F34F9FDF107C3A0902" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. pullus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having basally hyaline and apically infuscate wings (Key image 4A). Body ~ 5.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
